thread.title: Health insurer UnitedHealth's quarterly profit rises 30.6 pct

title: Health insurer UnitedHealth's quarterly profit rises 30.6 pct
text:
April 17, 2018 / 9:59 AM / Updated 24 minutes ago Health insurer UnitedHealth's quarterly profit rises 30.6 pct Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
April 17 (Reuters) - UnitedHealth Group Inc, the largest U.S. health insurer, reported a 30.6 percent rise in quarterly profit, driven by growth across its businesses. 
Net earnings attributable to shareholders rose to $2.84 billion, or $2.87 per share, in the first quarter ended March 31, from $2.17 billion or $2.23 per share, a year earlier. 
Total revenue rose 13.3 percent to $55.19 billion. (Reporting by Tamara Mathias in Bengaluru; Editing by Shounak Dasgupta)
